@user2:
I think we can squash this test and the one right above it by parametrizing on `squeeze`.  You can include a second parameter for the expected result i.e.

~~~python
@user1.mark.parametrize("squeeze,expected", [(True, <expected>, (False, <expected>)]
def test_from_frame_squeeze_param(squeeze, expected):
    df = pd.DataFrame([['a'], ['a'], ['b'], ['b']], columns=['L1'])
    result = pd.MultiIndex.from_frame(df, squeeze=squeeze)
    tm.assert_index_equal(expected, result)
~~~
